{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 11:42:06.292761", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submitted solution:\n- Anomaly detected: true\n- Faulty device(s): leaf_router_0_0\n- Root cause: host_static_blackhole\n\nRationale summary:\nA static/null (blackhole) route for 10.0.0.0/24 exists in the Linux kernel on leaf_router_0_0, overriding the expected connected route via eth2. This causes the leaf to drop traffic destined to its own subnet, breaking local host reachability and the return path for inter-subnet traffic. BGP control-plane is healthy across the fabric; issue is isolated to leaf_router_0_0’s L3 FIB.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 1977, "output_tokens": 134, "total_tokens": 2111, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1920}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
